-quran-exegesis-tafsir","tag-agreed-upon-muttafaqun-alayhi","tag-day-of-resurrection","tag-hereafter-akhirah","tag-manners-adab","tag-nation-ummah","tag-al-quran","tag-recitation-al-tilawah","tag-revelation-al-wahiy","tag-surah-al-nisa","tag-al-ummah","tag-weeping-al-baka"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-9i6","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":10899,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/03\/quran-seven-ahruf\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Ahruf: Quran has been revealed in seven dialects","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 3, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: I heard Hisham ibn Hakim reciting the Surat al-Furqan in a way different from how I recited it and how it was taught to me by the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. I was about to argue with him, but then I\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25027,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/06\/28\/surah-al-fatihah-enough\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Recitation: Surat al-Fatihah is enough, more is better","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 28, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ata\u2019 reported: Abu Huraira, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cIn every prayer is a recitation. Prayers that were recited aloud by the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, we have recited aloud to you, and what he recited silently, we have kept silent with you. Whoever recites\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11977,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/01\/recite-quran-month-seven-days\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Quran: Read entire Quran once every month","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 1, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cRead the Quran once in every month.\u201d I said, \u201cI have strength to do more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThen read it in twenty nights.\u201d I said, \u201cI have strength to do more.\u201d The Prophet said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4815,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/10\/this-day-completed-your-deen\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Arafat: This day I have completed your religion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: A man from the Jews said, \"O leader of the believers, there is a verse you recite in your book and, had it been revealed to us as Jews, we would have taken that day as a celebration.\" Umar said, \"Which verse is it?\" The man\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4288,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/05\/fajr-rakaat-light\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Fajr: The Prophet would sometimes pray lightly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would sometimes perform two cycles of prayer before the dawn prayer so lightly that I would say to myself, \"Did he recite Surat al-Fatihah?\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1165, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 724 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon)\u00a0according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17436,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/01\/prophet-recite-quran-nawm\/","url_meta":{"origin":35718,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Quran: The Prophet recites Quran before sleep","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 1, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would not sleep in his bed until he has recited Surat Bani Isra\u2019il and Al-Zumar. Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2920 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u